As part of the LIFE Ecotone project, specific measures have been implemented, limited to some sections of Paiva river (SCI Rio Paiva PTCON0059), to improving the conservation status of the species:
- recovery of 7 ha of habitat 91E0 * Alnus glutinosa and Fraxinus excelsior alluvial forests and increase of habitat area by 1.9 ha; creation of microhabitats with species-specific characteristics;  
- captive breeding of 30.923 juveniles of M. margaritifera using the infestation of 373 specimens of Salmo truta fario, one of the known hosts of  M. margaritifera (Reis & Araujo 2009); three repopulations on the Paiva River, with 12,104 released juveniles; 
- capture of 41 breeders in the Paiva river sub-basin and implementation of a new protocol for river trout reproduction;
- certified sport fishing concessions, with the elaboration of management plans and the respective regulation; 
- Placement of 5 informative panels in the intervention areas and poles.

Although these are not measures specifically taken for the conservation of the species, some existing regulatory measures that indirectly interfere with the conservation of the species may be listed, namely:
